<paragraph id="8BF7DA26FFA0CA5DAD9CFF05FCE6FEB1" blockId="2.[136,1452,159,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis id="B93C0634FFA0CA5DAD9CFF05FE9CFF25" bold="true" box="[189,262,231,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C48A1A5FFA0CA5DAC00FF05FE55FF25" authorityName="Y. S. Chen &amp; J. J. Liao" authorityYear="2021" box="[289,463,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loganiaceae" genus="Mitreola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B93C0634FFA0CA5DAC00FF05FE55FF25" box="[289,463,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Mitreola bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C48A1A5FFA0CA5DAFB3FF0AFAB7FF25" authority="Q. X. Ma, H. G. Ye &amp; F. W. Xing (2010: 42)" authorityName="Q. X. Ma, H. G. Ye &amp; F. W. Xing" authorityPageNumber="42" authorityYear="2010" box="[658,1325,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loganiaceae" genus="Mitreola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yangchunensis">
<emphasis id="B93C0634FFA0CA5DAFB3FF0AFD32FF25" box="[658,680,232,255]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B93C0634FFA0CA5DAF94FF05FCC8FF25" box="[693,850,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">yangchunensis</emphasis>
Q. X. Ma, H. G. Ye &amp; F. W. Xing (2010: 42)
</taxonomicName>
in its stems terete, stamens nearly inserted at the middle of corolla tube, capsules split near the middle and with two erect horns, but differs by its low height, leaf blades bullate and densely pilose on both surface, petiole longer and purple or green, veins in abaxial surface purple, calyces glabrous and purplish red (see 
<tableCitation id="C6CAEF9DFFA0CA5DAE3FFEB1FCF6FEB1" box="[798,876,339,363]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,555,579]" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological differences between M. bullata and M. yangchunensis." pageId="2" pageNumber="183" tableUuid="DF378AAEFFA0CA5DADA9FDC9FC74FD99">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF7DA26FFA0CA5DAD9CFE95FAFDFE21" blockId="2.[136,1452,159,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis id="B93C0634FFA0CA5DAD9CFE95FE30FE55" bold="true" box="[189,426,375,399]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation id="3B20D07BFFA0CA5DACE4FE95FAF9FE21" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3341000303" collectionCode="CR, IUCN" county="Yuanyang County" location="It" municipality="During" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" specimenCode="B1, 2, C2" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Yunnan">
<collectingMunicipality id="6B93405CFFA0CA5DACE4FE95FD8AFE55" box="[453,528,375,399]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">During</collectingMunicipality>
our one year’s fieldwork in southeastern 
<collectingRegion id="498C14C4FFA0CA5DAEF2FE9AFBBDFE55" box="[979,1063,376,399]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C48A1A5FFA0CA5DA912FE95FB7EFE55" authorityName="Y. S. Chen &amp; J. J. Liao" authorityYear="2021" box="[1075,1252,375,399]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loganiaceae" genus="Mitreola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B93C0634FFA0CA5DA912FE95FB7EFE55" box="[1075,1252,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Mitreola bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently found only from the 
<typeStatus id="54F36484FFA0CA5DAC01FE7EFED4FE6E" box="[288,334,412,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">type</typeStatus>
locality with no more than 100 individuals in 
<collectingCounty id="6296A2AAFFA0CA5DAE1CFE7EFC64FE69" box="[829,1022,411,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">Yuanyang County</collectingCounty>
. It is easily disturbed because its habitat is close to a town and farmland. 
<location id="8E978CFDFFA0CA5DACC9FE22FE62FE0D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E16B30FFA2CA5DADA9FABAFAFDFE21:8E978CFDFFA0CA5DACC9FE22FE62FE0D" box="[488,504,448,471]" county="Yuanyang County" municipality="During" name="It" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" stateProvince="Yunnan">It</location>
is considered to be 
<location id="8E978CFDFFA0CA5DAFF0FE5DFC26FE0D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E16B30FFA2CA5DADA9FABAFAFDFE21:8E978CFDFFA0CA5DAFF0FE5DFC26FE0D" box="[721,956,447,471]" county="Yuanyang County" municipality="During" name="Critically Endangered" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" stateProvince="Yunnan">Critically Endangered</location>
(
<collectionCode id="ED5942E3FFA0CA5DAEEDFE5DFC6BFE0D" box="[972,1009,447,471]" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" type="Herbarium">CR</collectionCode>
<specimenCode id="DBEE725DFFA0CA5DAED9FE5DFB83FE0D" box="[1016,1049,447,471]" collectionCode="B" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" type="Herbarium">B1</specimenCode>
, 
<specimenCode id="DBEE725DFFA0CA5DA904FE5DFBAEFE0D" box="[1061,1076,447,471]" collectionCode="CR" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" type="Herbarium">2</specimenCode>
a; 
<specimenCode id="DBEE725DFFA0CA5DA96CFE5DFBF7FE0D" box="[1101,1133,447,471]" collectionCode="C" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" type="Herbarium">C2</specimenCode>
a) because of its small size of only one population, which is vulnerable to human disturbance (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD9A7D7FFA0CA5DAE17FE01FAC1FE21" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[822,1371,483,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183" refId="ref2097" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." type="book" year="2019">
<collectionCode id="ED5942E3FFA0CA5DAE17FE01FCE3FE21" box="[822,889,483,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="183">IUCN</collectionCode>
Standards and Petitions Subcommittee 2019
</bibRefCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
